License and attribution information for Capra's software project

This software is distributed under the GPL-3 license. It is free,
open source, and has the following attribution requirements
(GPL Section 7):

- you agree to retain in Capra's software project and any
modifications to Capra's software project the copyright, author
attribution.
- you agree that Capra's software project and any modifications to
will, when used, display the attribution:
Based on "Club Capra - École de technologie supérieure" software
project (http://capra.etsmtl.ca).

What does this mean?

If you are modifying Capra's software project or adopting any source
code from Capra's software project for use in another application,
you must ensure that the copyright and attributions mentioned in the
license above appear in the code of your modified version or
application. These attributions must also appear when the package is
loaded (e.g., via "library" or "require").

